  "identifier": "urn:recipeimport:pdf:020e5142342e0bef5a211cd74199e35cae8dfbb1e66163f7856ffd071629ccb9:c14",
  "name": "HORSERADISH SOUP",
  "recipeIngredient": [
    "50g butter",
    "1 onion, peeled and roughly chopped",
    "1 large leek, trimmed, roughly chopped and washed",
    "1 tbsp pla1 n flou r"
  ],
  "recipeInstructions": [
    "1.5 litres hot vegetable stock salt and freshly ground black pepper lOOg freshly grated horseradish, or more to taste 1- 2 tbsp double cream Melt the butter in a large saucepan. Add the onion and leek, cover and cook gently without colouring for 3- 4 minutes, stirring every so often, to soften Stir in the flour and cook over a low heat for 30 seconds.",
    "then gradually stir in the vegetable stock. Bnng to the boil, season and simmer for 30 minutes.",
    "Add about two-thirds of the horseradish to the soup and simmer for 5 minutes, then take off the heat.",
    "Puree in a blender until smooth, then pass through a fine-meshed sieve into a clean saucepan.",
    "Taste for seasoning and the horseradish, adding more to taste. You don't need to blend the soup again the extra horseradish gives a nice te lure. Add the cream, bring back to a simmer and serve."
  ],
  "recipeYield": "Serves 4",
